NHL ENTRY DRAFT
June 27, 1998
Mathieu Biron
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT








Q.  (INAUDIBLE).

MATHIEU BIRON:   I said it was one of the most beautiful things today.


Q.  How do you feel about the--

MATHIEU BIRON:   I want to be drafted by an NHL team, so I'm really excited about being in L.A. now, the Kings.  I'm going to see more when I'm at the training camp.


Q.  About the draft --

MATHIEU BIRON:   The NHL sent out scouts rank me seven.  I might see that I'm going to be drafted sooner, but everything I want to be is being drafted by the NHL team in the first round.


Q.  (INAUDIBLE).

MATHIEU BIRON:   I think really last winter I just get caught up, but it is the end and I really don't know.


Q.  (INAUDIBLE)?

MATHIEU BIRON:   We were just joking because he was drafted 16th and I think he's 21.  So he was just welcome with me and they had a lot of fun.


Q.  Do you want the competition?

MATHIEU BIRON:   Yes.  Unfortunately we will.


Q.  (INAUDIBLE).

MATHIEU BIRON:   Actually --


Q.  On the team of Robertson might help you out?

MATHIEU BIRON:   Yes.  Because he was on the Montreal Canadiens and he come from Quebec and I just heard a lot about him and he's going to help me out a lot.  At the training camp.


